quran[32]{c,v,t,f}:
  86,1,"By the sky and the knocker",""
  86,2,"And what can make you know what is the knocker?",""
  86,3,"It is the piercing star[1].","[1] Whose light pierces through the darkness."
  86,4,"There is no soul but that it has over it a protector.",""
  86,5,"So let man observe from what he was created.",""
  86,6,"He was created from a fluid, ejected,",""
  86,7,"Emerging from between the backbone and the ribs.",""
  86,8,"Indeed, He [i.e., Allāh], to return him [to life], is Able.",""
  86,9,"The Day when secrets will be put on trial,[1]","[1] i.e., exposed, examined and judged."
  86,10,"Then he [i.e., man] will have no power or any helper.",""
  86,11,"By the sky which sends back[1]","[1] Rain, heat, sound waves, etc."
  86,12,"And [by] the earth which splits,[1]","[1] With plant growth or from geological rifts."
  86,13,"Indeed, it [i.e., the Qur’ān] is a decisive statement,",""
  86,14,"And it is not amusement.",""
  86,15,"Indeed, they are planning a plan,",""
  86,16,"But I am planning a plan.",""
  86,17,"So allow time for the disbelievers. Leave them awhile.[1]","[1] i.e., Do not be in haste for revenge, for you will see what will become of them."
  87,1,"Exalt the name of your Lord, the Most High,",""
  87,2,"Who created and proportioned",""
  87,3,"And who destined and [then] guided",""
  87,4,"And who brings out the pasture",""
  87,5,"And [then] makes it black stubble.",""
  87,6,"We will make you recite, [O Muḥammad], and you will not forget,",""
  87,7,"Except what Allāh should will. Indeed, He knows what is declared and what is hidden.",""
  87,8,"And We will ease you toward ease.[1]","[1] To the path of Allāh's religion, which is easy and natural, or toward Paradise, by giving opportunities for righteous deeds."
  87,9,"So remind, if the reminder should benefit;[1]","[1] i.e., wherever it will be heard and understood."
  87,10,"He who fears [Allāh] will be reminded.",""
  87,11,"But the wretched one will avoid it –",""
  87,12,"[He] who will [enter and] burn in the greatest Fire,",""
  87,13,"Neither dying therein nor living.",""
  87,14,"He has certainly succeeded who purifies himself",""
  87,15,"And mentions the name of his Lord and prays.",""
